====Noun====
{{en-noun|?}}

# The name of the fifth letter of many [[Semitic]] alphabets ([[Phoenician]], [[Aramaic]], [[Hebrew]], [[Syriac]], [[Arabic]] and others).
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1658|author=w:Thomas Browne|title=The Garden of Cyrus|page=210|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=2007
|passage=The same number in the Hebrew mysteries and Cabalistical accounts was the character of Generation; declared by the Letter '''''He''''', the fifth in their Alphabet.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1988|author=w:Milorad Pavić|translator=Christina Pribićević-Zorić|title=Dictionary of the Khazars|page=7|publisher=Vintage|year_published=1989
|passage=This Nehama claimed that in his own hand he recognized the consonant “'''he'''” of his Hebrew language, and in the letter “vav” his own male soul.}}
# The name of the first letter of the [[Old South Arabian]] abjad.

