==Manx==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|gv|sga|[[is]] [[ed]]|t=[[it]] [[is]] [[so]]}}. Compare {{cog|ga|sea}}, {{cog|gd|seadh}}.

===Particle===
{{head|gv|particle|dependent form|nee}}

# {{non-gloss|Present/future copula form}}
#: {{ux|gv|'''She''' ynseyder eh Juan.|John is a teacher.|inline=1}} {{qualifier|definition: predicate is indefinite}}
#: {{ux|gv|'''She''' Juan yn ynseyder.|John is the teacher.|inline=1}} {{qualifier|identification: predicate is definite}}
#: {{ux|gv|'''She''' mish honnick eh.|It's me who saw him.|inline=1}} {{qualifier|cleft sentence}}
#: {{ux|gv|'''She''' Juan ta ny ynseyder.|It's John who is a teacher.|inline=1}} {{qualifier|cleft sentence}}

====Usage notes====
Used in present and future sentences for identification or definition of a subject as the person/object identified in the predicate of the sentence. Used to introduce [[w:cleft sentence|cleft sentences]], which are extremely common in Manx. It is not a verb. For the particle that introduces adjectives, see {{m|gv|s'}}.

''She'' has no past tense; the appropriate conjugation of {{m|gv|ve}} must be used instead.
* {{ux|gv|Shen '''va''''n soilshey firrinagh.|That was the true light.}}

