====Determiner====
{{en-det}}

# {{lb|en|now|Southern England|_|dialect|or|nonstandard}} [[the|The]], [[those]]. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
#* '''1878''', Louis John Jennings, ''Field Paths and Green Lanes'', quoting an old East Sussex<!---"he spoke the East Sussex dialect"--> man:
#*: "'''They''' rooks as you see [...] only coom a few year agoo."
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1883|title=Judy, or the London serio-comic journal|volume=33|publisher=Harvard University|url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=8iEoAAAAYAAJ&dq=%22they%20Cockney%22&pg=PA190#v=onepage&q=%22they%20Cockney%22&f=false
|passage=Darn'd if '''they''' Cockney Chaps can zee there worn't nort but lie in him.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1895|title=Under the Chilterns: A Story of English Village Life
|passage=page 21: "But you spile [spoil] '''they''' gals - they won't be for no good, they won't."<br>page 30: "'Twas all about '''they''' rewks [rooks]," he sobbed.<br>page 54: "mucking the place up with '''they''' weeds"}}
#* '''1901''', Gwendoline Keats (of Devon), ''Tales of Dunstáble Weir'', page 55:
#*: "Bodies and souls," she cried, "if I didn't reckon to have hidden '''they''' boots safe from un in the stick-rick." "Off wi&apos; '''they''' tight-wasted shoes o' yours, Martha."
#* {{RQ:Welsh Trainspotting|page=114|passage=Forty quid a fuckin ticket. No shy '''they''' British Rail cunts, ah kin fuckin tell ye.}}
# {{lb|en|US|_|dialects|including|AAVE}} [[their|Their]]. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1974|author=Arthur Hippler|title=Hunter's Point: a black ghetto in America|page=88|passage=MARY ELLEN is a different case from the others. She has five children and, she claims: "I don't know who '''they''' father is. I ain't never kept track. They is always another one. You know, I can catch me a guy[.]"}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=2002|author=w:Eminem|title={{w|Sing for the Moment |Sing for the Moment}}
|passage=But all '''they''' kids be listenin' to me religiously / So I'm signin' CDs while police fingerprint me}}
#* {{quote-song|en|title=Energy|year=2015|album=If You’re Reading This It’s Too Late|artist=Drake|passage=I got bitches askin' me about the code for the Wi-Fi / So they can talk about '''they''' timeline / And show me pictures of '''they''' friends}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2016|author=w:Alan Moore|title=Jerusalem|publisher=Liveright|year_published=2016|page=175
|passage=He guessed one of the well-off people living in these houses must have took a shine to Cody and decided how he'd look good stuck up on '''they''' roof.}}

