====Pronoun====
{{en-pron}}

# {{lb|en|US|_|dialectal}} [[there|There]] {{qualifier|especially as an expletive subject of be}}. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1889|author=w:James Whitcomb Riley|title=Pipes o' Pan
|passage='''They'''’s music in the twitter of the bluebird and the jay.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1974|author=Arthur Hippler|title=Hunter's Point: a black ghetto in America|page=88|passage=MARY ELLEN is a different case from the others. She has five children and, she claims: "I don't know who they father is. I ain't never kept track. '''They''' is always another one. You know, I can catch me a guy[.]"}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2000|author=Janice Giles|title=Hill Man|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=nvmjVapqBOYC&lpg=PA58&dq=%22they%20ain't%20nothin%22&pg=PA58#v=onepage&q=%22they%20ain't%20nothin%22&f=false|page=58
|passage='''They''' ain’t nothin’ wrong with that.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Christian Carvajal|title=Lightfall|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=J3kkoYvglrQC&lpg=PA82&dq=%22they%20ain't%20nothin%22&pg=PA82#v=onepage&q=%22they%20ain't%20nothin%22&f=false|page=82
|passage=But '''they''' ain’t nothin’ in there you didn’t already have.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2010|author=Alessandro Portelli|title=They Say in Harlan County: An Oral History|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=uOU6n6zP1W8C&lpg=PA207&dq=%22they%20a%20lot%22&pg=PA207#v=onepage&q=%22they%20a%20lot%22&f=false|page=207
|passage=Well, '''they'''’s a lot of ‘em didn’t survive, if you believe me.}}

